main event: Multiple witnesses observed 5-6 unidentified objects moving at high speeds over Lake Winnebago, Wisconsin on August 26, 1959.
interesting points: The objects appeared as single lights, moving at speeds around 40 mph.
The objects would climb about 4-5 degrees, then move horizontally for 8-10 seconds before fading out.
Additional objects were sighted near the Big Dipper constellation, with one object moving from one end of the Big Dipper to the other in about 3 seconds.
The objects were described as having a faint, yellowish-white light, about as bright as a first magnitude star.
The sighting lasted from around 8:45 pm to 9:15 pm.
sighted object: Multiple unidentified lights/objects in the sky
witnesses: Multiple civilian witnesses in a boat
